BAJRMAN – Smart Car SeatBelt Safety System

A Smart Seatbelt Safety System for an RC Car that restricts vehicle speed when the seatbelt is worn incorrectly.

The system uses ESP32, Capacitive Touch Sensors, Blynk IoT, and a Wireless Relay Module to simulate a real-world automotive safety mechanism where vehicle performance is limited if the seatbelt is not secured properly.

Project Concept

This project demonstrates a vehicle safety logic:

Seatbelt secured → Full speed allowed

Seatbelt not secured → Speed restricted

The ESP32 reads capacitive touch sensors placed on the seatbelt system.
Based on the detected pattern, the ESP32:

Updates the Blynk IoT dashboard

Sends a signal to a wireless relay remote

Changes the relay state (NC / NO) to restrict speed.

System Architecture
Seatbelt Touch Sensors
        │
        ▼
      ESP32
        │
 ┌──────┴────────┐
 ▼               ▼
Blynk IoT    Wireless Relay
Dashboard        Remote
                    │
                    ▼
                Relay (NC/NO)
                    │
                    ▼
                RC Car Motor
Voltage Regulation

The RC system uses higher voltage than the control electronics.

A Buck Converter is used to:

Reduce voltage

Stabilize power supply

Protect ESP32 and relay module

Hardware Components

ESP32

4 × TTP223 Capacitive Touch Sensors

Wireless Relay Module

Buck Converter

RC Car Motor System

Lithium Battery / Power Supply

Relay (NO / NC control)

Seatbelt Detection Logic

Four capacitive sensors simulate seatbelt connection points.

Sensor Combination	Condition	Result
C1 + C3	Correct belt	Full speed
C2 + C4	Correct belt	Full speed
Any other combination	Incorrect belt	Speed limited

If the belt is worn incorrectly:

ESP32 triggers relay NO state

Vehicle enters restricted speed mode

Blynk IoT Integration

The system is connected to Blynk IoT platform for monitoring.

Features

Real-time seatbelt sensor monitoring

Live belt status indicator

Remote vehicle status display

Cloud-based IoT dashboard

Virtual Pins Used
Virtual Pin	Function
V0	Sensor C1
V1	Sensor C2
V2	Sensor C3
V3	Sensor C4

The Blynk dashboard shows:

Sensor activation

Seatbelt secured status

System connection status

