Web Interface Features

The interface simulates the real system behavior.

Seatbelt Sensor Simulation

Buttons represent the capacitive sensors:

C1   C2   C3   C4

Indicator lights:

Green Light → Seatbelt secured

Red Light → Seatbelt not secured

RC Car Controller

Control buttons:

Forward

Backward

Left

Right

Stop

Speed Restriction System
Seatbelt Status	Allowed Speed
Secured	100%
Not Secured	35%

A speedometer bar visually displays the speed restriction.

ESP32 Working Logic

ESP32 performs the following tasks:

Reads input from touch sensors

Detects seatbelt pattern

Updates Blynk IoT dashboard

Sends signal to wireless relay remote

Relay switches between NC and NO state

Car speed is restricted when belt is incorrect

Safety Logic
Correct Seatbelt
        ↓
Relay NC State
        ↓
Full Speed Mode

Incorrect Seatbelt
        ↓
Relay NO State
        ↓
Restricted Speed Mode
